<paragraph id="8B9898347E54FFD8FF3F75D5DB1FF8EC" blockId="38.[192,1025,1791,1815]" box="[192,1025,1791,1815]" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B95344267E54FFD8FF3F75D5DE69F8EC" bold="true" box="[192,375,1791,1815]" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">
<typeStatus id="549C26967E54FFD8FF3F75D5DE1AF8EC" box="[192,260,1791,1815]" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">Type</typeStatus>
species.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E54FFD8FE8175D5DCE0F8EC" authority="Austin and A. Warren, 2009" authorityName="Austin and A. Warren" authorityYear="2009" box="[382,1022,1791,1815]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Buzyges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mellanaformis">
<emphasis id="B95344267E54FFD8FE8175D5DD84F8EC" box="[382,666,1791,1815]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">Buzyges mellanaformis</emphasis>
Austin and A. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6E5C57E54FFD8FCAD742ADCE0F8EC" author="Warren, A. D. &amp; J. R. Ogawa &amp; A. V. Z. Brower" box="[850,1022,1791,1815]" journalOrPublisher="Revised classification of the family Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera: Hesperioidea) based on combined molecular and morphological data. Systematic Entomology" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" pagination="467 - 523" part="34" refId="ref28632" refString="Warren, A. D., J. R. Ogawa, and A. V. Z. Brower. 2009. Revised classification of the family Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera: Hesperioidea) based on combined molecular and morphological data. Systematic Entomology 34 (3): 467 - 523." type="journal article" year="2009">Warren, 2009</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9898347E54FFD9FF3F7405DBCDF8C2" blockId="38.[192,1440,1839,1929]" lastBlockId="39.[192,1440,1632,1849]" lastPageId="39" lastPageNumber="38" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B95344267E54FFD8FF3F7405DE4BF8BC" bold="true" box="[192,341,1839,1863]" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">Definition.</emphasis>
Not monophyletic with 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E54FFD8FD70741ADB2CF8B3" authority="Godman, [1900]" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1900" box="[655,1074,1839,1864]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Buzyges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="idothea">
<emphasis id="B95344267E54FFD8FD70741ADC44F8BC" box="[655,858,1839,1863]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">Buzyges idothea</emphasis>
Godman, [1900]
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus id="549C26967E54FFD8FB89741ADBB2F8B3" box="[1142,1196,1840,1864]" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E54FFD8FAC3741ADE99F893" authority="Godman, [1900]" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1900" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Buzyges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E54FFD8FAC3741ADABEF8BC" box="[1340,1440,1840,1863]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">Buzyges</emphasis>
Godman, [1900]
</taxonomicName>
, this genus is placed in a different clade instead (
<figureCitation id="131C84B17E54FFD8FC0E747ADB57F893" box="[1009,1097,1872,1896]" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="39.[192,275,1562,1584]" captionTargetBox="[192,1438,215,1528]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[192,1440,213,1528]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="Figure 13. Genomic trees of Hesperiina, Pericharini and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677261" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677261/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Detailed diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E54FFD8FA94747ADE5BF873" authorityName="Austin and A. Warren" authorityYear="2009" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Buzyges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mellanaformis">
<emphasis id="B95344267E54FFD8FA94747ADE5BF873" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">mellanaformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
given by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6E5C57E54FFD8FE42745ADC3EF872" author="Austin and Warren" box="[445,800,1904,1929]" firstAuthor="Austin" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" pagination="1 - 55" refId="ref26459" refString="Austin, G. T., and A. D. Warren. 2009. New looks at and for Onespa, Buzyges, and Librita (Lepidop- tera: Hesperiidae: Hesperiinae), with new combinations and descriptions of a new genus and six new species. Insecta Mundi 89: 1 - 55." type="journal article" year="2009">Austin and Warren (2009:28</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 70, 82, 90) can be applied to this genus (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6E5C57E54FFD9FAB2745ADE89F982" author="Austin and Warren" firstAuthor="Austin" lastPageId="39" lastPageNumber="38" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" pagination="1 - 55" refId="ref26459" refString="Austin, G. T., and A. D. Warren. 2009. New looks at and for Onespa, Buzyges, and Librita (Lepidop- tera: Hesperiidae: Hesperiinae), with new combinations and descriptions of a new genus and six new species. Insecta Mundi 89: 1 - 55." type="journal article" year="2009">Austin and Warren 2009</bibRefCitation>
). In brief, differs from related genera by long antennae, the lack of stigma, short tegumen and uncus and relatively small valva with broad trapezoid harpe (shared with 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E55FFD9FB4A75ABDA06F963" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1900" box="[1205,1304,1665,1688]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Buzyges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E55FFD9FB4A75ABDA06F963" box="[1205,1304,1665,1688]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">Buzyges</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), but penis narrower and cornuti are smaller than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E55FFD9FD35758BDC33F943" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1900" box="[714,813,1697,1720]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Buzyges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E55FFD9FD35758BDC33F943" box="[714,813,1697,1720]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">Buzyges</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see Fig. 70 and 
<quantity id="4CDF35D17E55FFD9FBFC758BDB5CF943" box="[1027,1090,1696,1721]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0827999999999998" pageId="39" pageNumber="38" unit="in" value="82.0">82 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6E5C57E55FFD9FBB4758ADA82F942" author="Austin and Warren" box="[1099,1436,1696,1721]" firstAuthor="Austin" pageId="39" pageNumber="38" pagination="1 - 55" refId="ref26459" refString="Austin, G. T., and A. D. Warren. 2009. New looks at and for Onespa, Buzyges, and Librita (Lepidop- tera: Hesperiidae: Hesperiinae), with new combinations and descriptions of a new genus and six new species. Insecta Mundi 89: 1 - 55." type="journal article" year="2009">Austin and Warren (2009))</bibRefCitation>
, mid- and hind-tibiae without spines characteristic of 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E55FFD9FCB775EBDCB5F923" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1900" box="[840,939,1729,1752]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Buzyges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E55FFD9FCB775EBDCB5F923" box="[840,939,1729,1752]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">Buzyges</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and forewing outer margin more convex. In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly386.7.5:A874T, aly207.4.6:A367T, aly320.7.8:G428A, aly128.6.20:C131C (not G), aly708.6.1:A1197A (not G), aly1838.58.4:T1070T (not C), aly536.174.1:A1825A (not C), aly2582.33.4:A512A (not T), aly3071.1.1:C135C (not T).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF58C8BC7E55FFD9FF3F7530DBE0F9CA" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677261" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3677261" box="[192,1278,1562,1585]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677261/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="38" startId="39.[192,275,1562,1584]" targetBox="[192,1438,215,1528]" targetPageId="39">
<paragraph id="8B9898347E55FFD9FF3F7530DBE0F9CA" blockId="39.[192,1278,1562,1585]" box="[192,1278,1562,1585]" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="B95344267E55FFD9FF3F7530DE22F9D4" bold="true" box="[192,316,1562,1584]" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">Figure 13.</emphasis>
Genomic trees of Hesperiina, 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E55FFD9FD777531DC1BF9CA" authorityName="Grishin" authorityYear="2019" box="[648,773,1563,1585]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Pericharini">Pericharini</taxonomicName>
and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C33DCBBF7E55FFD6FF3F747ADC21FED9" lastPageId="40" lastPageNumber="39" pageId="39" pageNumber="38" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B9898347E55FFD9FF3F747ADDA5F873" blockId="39.[192,1440,1872,1929]" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="B95344267E55FFD9FF3F747ADE45F893" bold="true" box="[192,347,1872,1896]" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is a feminine noun in the nominative singular, formed from the 
<typeStatus id="549C26967E55FFD9FAF4747BDA5EF892" box="[1291,1344,1873,1897]" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">type</typeStatus>
species original name 
<emphasis id="B95344267E55FFD9FE8D745BDEBCF873" box="[370,418,1905,1928]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">Buz</emphasis>
[yges m] 
<emphasis id="B95344267E55FFD9FDF7745ADD2BF873" box="[520,565,1904,1928]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">ella</emphasis>
[naformis].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9898347E5AFFD6FF3F73F3DDDDFF0A" blockId="40.[192,707,217,242]" box="[192,707,217,242]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis id="B95344267E5AFFD6FF3F73F3DEAEFF0A" bold="true" box="[192,432,217,241]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">Species included.</emphasis>
Only the 
<typeStatus id="549C26967E5AFFD6FDD673F0DD40FF09" box="[553,606,218,242]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">type</typeStatus>
species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9898347E5AFFD6FF3F7220DC21FED9" blockId="40.[192,831,266,290]" box="[192,831,266,290]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis id="B95344267E5AFFD6FF3F7220DE62FED9" bold="true" box="[192,380,266,290]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">Parent taxon.</emphasis>
Subtribe Hesperiina Latreille, 1809.
</paragraph>
